            <!-- Contents -->
            <noteGrp type="workDesc">
               <note type="description">Treatise on four kinds of knowers (ʿulamāʾ) at the Well
                     of Arīn (axis mundi): those of the west (maghrib), those of the east (mashriq),
                     those of the north (shimāl) and those of the south (yamīn), and their kinds of
                     knowledge. See also FM 1:38-41.</note>
               <note type="structure"/>
               <note type="contentsNote"/>
            </noteGrp>
            <!-- Stemmatics -->
            <note type="stemmatics">OY cites seven mss. Verified by one historic ms.,Veliyuddin
                  51 (762H, copied from an original composed in Damascus in 602H). Milli 2988 is the
                  same text, but the other two mss. we have consulted are different texts. Confused
                  with RG 34 and others. Further work needed. Further mss identified by JC: Tunis,
                  Dar al-Kutub al-Wataniya 641, and Escurial ms 417 / 4 (f. 117-131?)</note>
